COMP2011_ch10_8:
Initialization of a struct Variable
Just like an array variable, a struct variable can be initialized
when it is defined using the initializer list with braces.
Point a = { 24.5, 123.0 };
If it is not initialized during its definition, later its members
can only be modified using separate memberwise assignments
or struct-struct assignment (memberwise copy).
b.x = 24.5;
// Separate memberwise assignments
b.y = 123.0;
// if no similar object to copy from
// struct-struct assignment to copy a's members to b's
b = a;
For relatively big structures, write a function to do that.
